rules.ruleString: (Must have passed an (I/W) unit in {BMA1901} and  Must have passed an (I/W) unit in {NUR1010, NUR1101})
Must be enrolled in course version {3562, 3953, 4514}

description: Students learning will focus on well women's experiences of recognising pregnancy, their response to becoming pregnant, the changes encountered from early pregnancy through to the early weeks after birth, the midwife's roles relating to health assessment, health promotion, primary level health counselling, and working with well women during childbearing.
faculty: Faculty of Medicine, Nursing and Health Sciences
